<h2>Chapter 4: On-Page SEO for Chiropractic Websites</h2>
<p>Most chiropractic websites make the same mistake: one generic "Services" page listing everything. That approach targets zero specific keywords.</p>
<h3>Create Individual Service Pages</h3>
<p>Every treatment and condition you address needs its own page. Each page should include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>H1 title</strong> with the treatment/condition + city name</li>
<li><strong>200 to 500 words</strong> of unique content explaining the treatment, who it helps, and what to expect</li>
<li><strong>A clear CTA</strong> (book an appointment, call now)</li>
<li><strong>Schema markup</strong> for MedicalBusiness and the specific service</li>
<li><strong>Internal links</strong> to related conditions and treatments</li>
</ul>
<p>A chiropractic practice offering 8 treatments across 3 service areas should have 24+ individual pages, not 1 generic page.</p>
<h3>Title Tag and Meta Description Formulas</h3>
<p><strong>Title tag formula:</strong></p>
<pre><code>[Treatment/Condition] | [Practice Name] [City]
</code></pre>
<p>Example: <code>Sciatica Treatment | Austin Spine &amp; Wellness Austin TX</code></p>
<p><strong>Meta description formula:</strong></p>
<pre><code>[What you treat] + [what makes you different] + [CTA]. [Trust signal].
</code></pre>
<p>Example: "Sciatica relief through targeted spinal adjustments. Same-day appointments available. Call (512) 555-0100. 200+ 5-star Google reviews."</p>
<p>For more on writing effective meta tags, see our guide on <a href="/blog/write-meta-descriptions/">how to write meta descriptions</a>.</p>
<h3>Header Hierarchy</h3>
<p>Structure every service page with a clear header hierarchy:</p>
<pre><code>H1: Chiropractor for [Condition] in [City]
  H2: What Causes [Condition]
  H2: How Chiropractic Treats [Condition]
    H3: [Technique 1]
    H3: [Technique 2]
  H2: What to Expect at Your First Visit
  H2: Insurance and Pricing
  H2: Book Your Appointment
</code></pre>
<h3>Page Speed and Mobile</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.chirospring.com/articles/why-local-seo-matters-for-chiropractors">70% of chiropractic searches happen on mobile devices</a>. If your site takes more than 3 seconds to load, half your visitors leave.</p>
